The head of the astragalus articulates ex­ clusively with the navicular in most eutherians, but in anagalids (
Simpson, 1931
; 
Bohlin, 1951
) and macroscelideans (
Szalay, 1985
) it also has a small contact with the cuboid. As in 

Gomphos

, the contact is absent in lagomorphs (
Szalay, 1985
) but is present in 

Mimolagus

(
Bleefeld and McKenna, 1985
; 
Szalay, 1985
).
